WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.587
Diagnosis follows a stepwise approach.

00:00:02.587 --> 00:00:05.692
Initial workup includes ECG, troponin, BNP,

00:00:05.692 --> 00:00:08.279
CBC, CMP, and inflammatory markers.

00:00:08.279 --> 00:00:11.384
Cardiac MRI using Lake Louise Criteria

00:00:11.384 --> 00:00:14.489
is the diagnostic test of choice

00:00:14.489 --> 00:00:17.594
in hemodynamically stable patients, identifying edema,

00:00:17.594 --> 00:00:20.181
hyperemia, and late gadolinium enhancement.

00:00:20.181 --> 00:00:23.286
Endomyocardial biopsy is indicated for presentations

00:00:23.286 --> 00:00:26.390
with hemodynamic compromise, sustained arrhythmia, heart

00:00:26.390 --> 00:00:29.495
block, or failure to improve —

00:00:29.495 --> 00:00:32.600
critical for identifying actionable histologic subtypes.
